cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.CC 

This paper deals with a machine learning problem involving bandits, optimization, and constraints. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper presents algorithms for solving a contextual bandit problem with a concave objective function. Other relevant sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper involves designing algorithms for optimization problems. Additionally, the paper involves information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC) in analyzing the performance of the algorithms.
